    "department": "Sales Support",
    "description": "LIFE AT UIPATH\n\nThe people at UiPath believe in the transformative power of automation to change how the world works. We’re committed to creating category-leading enterprise software that unleashes that power.\n\nTo make that happen, we need people who are curious, self-propelled, generous, and genuine. People who love being part of a fast-moving, fast-thinking growth company. And people who care—about each other, about UiPath, and about our larger purpose.\n\nCould that be you?\n\nYour Mission:\nAs a Federal Strategic Engagement Executive, you will transform industry insights into high-impact assets and programs that drive success in the Federal space. Reporting to the AVP of Public Sector, you'll craft clear narratives for Agentic AI transformation functions within our Federal portfolio. Your work will help our teams and clients navigate this complex space while shaping the next wave of AI and Agentic workloads in a highly regulated landscape.\n\nWhat you'll do at UiPath:\n\n - Be a part of a market-leading AI company transforming the Public Sector\n\n - Create and maintain Federal narratives and sales-ready assets including one-pagers, talk tracks, and discovery guides tailored to buyers\n\n - Develop light value framing with problem statements, outcomes, and ROI angles specific to the Federal space\n\n - Package and deliver how-to-sell kits by use case, running enablement sessions for internal teams and tracking asset adoption\n\n - Build partner messaging kits for priority GSIs/SIs/ISVs with aligned value propositions and example architectures\n\n - Gather voice-of-customer inputs to inform Vertical packaging and prioritization while supporting product launches\n\n - Join discovery and qualification calls to capture customer objectives and align teams on demo storyboards\n\n - Maintain content hygiene with version control and build lightweight dashboards for tracking asset usage and enablement reach\n\nWhat you'll bring to the team:\n\n - 10+ years of Federal government experience focused on: B2B software, consulting, product marketing, or sales enablement\n\n - Experience working with Centers for Medicare and Medicaid Services (CMS) and Department of Health and Human Services (HHS)\n\n - Solid understanding of workflows and strong written/verbal communication skills\n\n - Comfort with AI \u0026 automation concepts and ability to translate technical ideas into business value\n\n - Proven project management skills with ability to juggle multiple deliverables and meet deadlines\n\n - Bachelor's degree or equivalent experience\n\n - Excitement to be involved with a generational technology and how it can change the Federal space\n\nNice-to-Have Skills\n\n - Experience creating sales enablement content such as battlecards and discovery guides\n\n - Familiarity with Salesforce and content hubs like Highspot\n\n - Exposure to partner ecosystems and co-marketing/co-sell motions\n\nMaybe you don’t tick all the boxes above—but still think you’d be great for the job? Go ahead, apply anyway. Please. Because we know that experience comes in all shapes and sizes—and passion can’t be learned.\n\nMany of our roles allow for flexibility in when and where work gets done. Depending on the needs of the business and the role, the number of hybrid, office-based, and remote workers will vary from team to team. Applications are assessed on a rolling basis and there is no fixed deadline for this requisition. The application window may change depending on the volume of applications received or may close immediately if a qualified candidate is selected.\n\nWe value a range of diverse backgrounds, experiences and ideas. We pride ourselves on our diversity and inclusive workplace that provides equal opportunities to all persons regardless of age, race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, and expression, national origin, disability, neurodiversity, military and/or veteran status, or any other protected classes. Additionally, UiPath provides reasonable accommodations for candidates on request and respects applicants' privacy rights. To review these and other legal disclosures, visit our privacy policy https://www.uipath.com/legal/trust-and-security/privacy-policy.",
